caption: Delicious tacos! So good that I forgot to take a picture of them, specially the Al Pastor.

Good food at reasonable prices! This bodega is located within an airstream trailer. I had chicken quesadillas there. The guy, Lautaro, said it would take a bit over 10 minutes to freshly make it, and he was right. Taste and size were great for the $ 9.63 it cost. They do not accept cash; credit cards only. Ironically - please look up my pictures - the airstream bodega sell food for take away just 20 feet distant from an art installation by Paula Crown, named Jokester 2: her 10-foot crushed red solo cup is a call for environmental activism and the end of single-use plastic.

Ordered pick up on Postmates where the restaurant confirmed my order and said it was ready for pick up. Arrived to a very rude woman watching youtube and said they didnt have my food and she didnt know what to tell me so I lost my money on Postmates. When I tried to order food outside of Postmates in person she told me they weren’t serving food.. at 4pm
